trans-unit.source: Represents the <see langword="<CipherData>" /> element in XML encryption.
trans-unit.target: Representa el elemento <see langword="<CipherData>" /> del cifrado XML.

trans-unit.source: This class cannot be inherited.
trans-unit.target: Esta clase no puede heredarse.

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.CipherData> class represents the `<CipherData>` element in XML encryption.
trans-unit.target: El <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.CipherData> clase representa el `<CipherData>` elemento en el cifrado XML.

trans-unit.source: It is a required element that provides the encrypted data.
trans-unit.target: Es un elemento necesario que proporciona los datos cifrados.

trans-unit.source: It must either contain the encrypted data as base64-encoded text of the `<CipherValue>` element, or provide a reference to an external location containing the encrypted data using the `<CipherReference>` element.
trans-unit.target: O bien debe contener los datos cifrados como texto codificado en base64 de la `<CipherValue>` elemento, o proporcionar una referencia a una ubicación externa que contiene los datos cifrados mediante el `<CipherReference>` elemento.

trans-unit.source: In many cases, you do not need to directly create a new instance of the <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.CipherData> class.
trans-unit.target: En muchos casos, no es necesario crear directamente una nueva instancia de la <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.CipherData> clase.

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.SignedXml.EncryptedXml%2A>, <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.EncryptedData>, and <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.EncryptedKey> classes create instances for you.
trans-unit.target: El <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.SignedXml.EncryptedXml%2A>, <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.EncryptedData>, y <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.EncryptedKey> clases crean instancias para usted.

trans-unit.source: A <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.CipherData> object can have either a <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.CipherReference> property or a <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.CipherData.CipherValue%2A> property, but not both.
trans-unit.target: A <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.CipherData> objeto puede tener un <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.CipherReference> propiedad o un <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.CipherData.CipherValue%2A> propiedad, pero no ambos.

trans-unit.source: A <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.CryptographicException> is thrown if both are assigned to a <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.CipherData> object.
trans-unit.target: A <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.CryptographicException> se produce si ambos están asignados a un <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.CipherData> objeto.
